benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: PUT Method: Valid Request scenarios are well covered (TC01, TC14) including happy path and header variations.
PUT Method: Non-Existing Resource and Not Found handling (TC03 malformed-id, TC04 non-existent bundle) covered.

PUT Method: Validation/Error scenarios (TC02 missing header, TC06 missing body, TC07 malformed JSON, TC08 missing externalKey, TC11 empty externalKey, TC15 no bundles, TC10/TC19/TC20 various edge cases) covered.
PUT Method: Concurrency and performance considerations (TC17 concurrent updates, TC23 performance under load, TC16 large payload, TC09 extra fields) addressed.
Backward compatibility and regression: Legacy client compatibility and regression scenarios (TC22, TC18) covered.
gaps: Partial updates: No explicit test ensuring PUT rejects partial updates or ignores unspecified fields beyond body handling (beyond TC09 extra fields).
Caching/ETag behavior: No tests around caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Rate limiting: No tests verifying rate limiting or throttling behavior under rapid requests.
Pagination: Not applicable for this endpoint; no pagination tests needed here.
Authorization edge variants: While TC12 covers unauthorized, there could be broader coverage around token refresh or expired tokens not explicitly tested.
recommendations: Add a dedicated test ensuring strict separation of allowed fields on PUT (verify that unspecified fields are ignored or rejected as per API policy).
Add tests for caching behavior: verify ETag/Cache-Control headers if the API uses caching semantics.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to confirm proper handling under bursty traffic.
Expand authorization tests to cover expired/invalid tokens and token refresh flows, if applicable.
Consider a focused test for edge-case content validation of externalKey (e.g., allowed/disallowed characters per policy) beyond existing TC19/TC20 variations.
